00:03:05.300 --> 00:03:08.250
But, all right, so,
Parsec in Star Wars

00:03:08.250 --> 00:03:10.480
sounds like it's a unit of time.

00:03:10.480 --> 00:03:12.030
It's actually a
unit of distance.

00:03:12.030 --> 00:03:14.430
And the way it works is
you talk about the distance

00:03:14.430 --> 00:03:19.030
between our sun and some
other astronomical object that

00:03:19.030 --> 00:03:24.780
has a 1-second arc degree
difference in parallax angle.

00:03:24.780 --> 00:03:27.950
Now that essentially means
that when we look at the star

00:03:27.950 --> 00:03:30.200
and we compare it
to the sun, and we

00:03:30.200 --> 00:03:33.060
do that again at another
point on the Earth's orbit,

00:03:33.060 --> 00:03:34.900
we get that 1-second arc degree.

00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:38.560
That distance actually ends
up being 3.26 light-years.

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:39.910
So it's even longer.

00:03:39.910 --> 00:03:41.540
So there you go.

